GateDocument.TextWithNodes: << " Well then, " said Don Quixote, " the same thing happens in the comedy and life of this world, where some play emperors, others play popes, and, in short, all the characters that can be brought into a play; but when it is over, that is to say when life ends, death strips them all of the garments that distinguish one from the other, and all are equal in the grave. "
